string<->number

primer, ch.11

(1) num-to-string conversion
    - printf() (see string->output)
    - sprintf() (see->string->functions)
(2) string-to-num conversion
    - scanf() (see string->input)
    - atoi() (alphanumeric to integer) [stdlib.h]
        - arg: string
        - returns the corresponding integer val
        - e.g. see command-line args
    - strtol() converts string to a long [stdlib.h]
    - strtod() converts string to double [stdlib.h]

EXAMPLE
(1)
printf("num: %d", 3);
(2)
#include <stdlib.h>
char argv[] = "3";
int i = atoi(argv);
printf("int: %d", i); // int: 3
